              <h3>Top-Freezer Refrigerators</h3>
              <p>
                Top freezer refrigerators are the choice, for homes with the
                freezer section located above the main fridge area. These models
                are known for being budget friendly and energy efficient
                compared to types. When it comes to maintenance issues with the
                defrost system can cause ice buildup. Impact cooling efficiency.
                Another common problem is worn out door seals, which can lead to
                temperature fluctuations and higher energy usage. Regular upkeep
                like cleaning the condenser coils and checking the door gaskets
                can help extend the lifespan of these appliances.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Bottom-Freezer Refrigerators</h3>
              <p>
                Bottom freezer refrigerators have a freezer compartment below
                the fridge section making it easier to access used items. These
                models often come with drawers or baskets in the freezer. These
                sliding mechanisms may sometimes encounter problems. Since the
                freezer is positioned lower, it's important to clean the
                condenser coils to prevent cooling issues. Additionally, issues
                like ice makers and temperature control malfunctions may arise
                over time. Performing tasks such as defrosting the freezer and
                examining door seals can help prevent these issues from
                escalating.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Side-by-Side Refrigerators</h3>
              <p>
                Side, by side refrigerators feature a split design where the
                freezer and refrigerator compartments are positioned next to
                each other for access. While this layout allows retrieval of
                refrigerated items the compartments are often narrower posing
                challenges for storing larger items effectively. Common repair
                issues with side by side models typically involve problems with
                the ice maker, water dispenser and defrost system due to lines
                or faulty valves. Ensuring that the condenser coils are kept
                clean and that the door seals remain effective can help prevent
                many of these issues.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
