                French door refrigerators combine elements of freezer and side
                by side models by featuring two refrigerator doors on top and a
                freezer drawer below for storage capacity. This configuration
                provides space for storing food items while offering convenient
                accessibility. However, the intricate design of door models
                often leads to a likelihood of requiring repairs, such as issues
                with ice makers, water dispensers, and temperature control
                systems. Moreover, the seals on the door resulting in energy
                inefficoors may wear out faster than those on models,iency over
                time. Regular maintenance tasks like cleaning the condenser
                coils and checking door gaskets can play a role, in preserving
                the appliances performance.
              </p>
            </div>

