                      <b>Frost Build-Up: </b>Excessive frost in the freezer
                      compartment might be due to a faulty defrost system, door
                      gasket, or other issues that need professional attention.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Constant Running: </b>If your refrigerator is
                      constantly running without cycling off, it can lead to
                      higher energy bills and wear out the compressor
                      prematurely. This may be due to issues with the condenser
                      coils, defrost timer, or thermostat.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Electrical Problems: </b>If your refrigerator is
                      experiencing electrical issues, such as tripping the
                      circuit breaker or flickering lights, it's best to call a
                      professional to avoid potential hazards.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Unresponsive Controls: </b>If the control panel or
                      thermostat is unresponsive, it could indicate an issue
                      with the electronic control board or wiring.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Door Seal Issues: </b>If the door seals are damaged or
                      not sealing properly, it can cause the refrigerator to
                      work harder to maintain the temperature, leading to higher
                      energy consumption and potential damage.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Ice Maker Problems: </b>If the ice maker isn't
                      producing ice, is producing too little, or the ice cubes
                      are malformed, it could indicate a problem with the water
                      line, filter, or ice maker unit itself.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Unpleasant Odors: </b>Persistent unpleasant odors that
                      cleaning doesn't resolve might indicate mold, mildew, or a
                      chemical leak, which needs professional diagnosis and
                      repair.
                    </li>
